data.title: Wonderful service
data.text: We go to subway often, it was our first time at the Apache mall and I just want subway to know that Mike and his coworker who were working on 2/13/16 at 2:30pm were absolutely outstanding individuals who represented subway well. Thank you for brightening our day!

data.title: Yummy
data.text: I had a meatless breakfast biscuit. It was fresh and delicious! The lady helping me seamed like perhaps she needed a little more sleep, but she was very friendly. I eat at Subway often, and my whole family loves it.

data.title: Quik stop for breakfast
data.text:
I like Subway flatbread egg sandwiches - unfortunately they don't like me so much (too many carbs in the bread unless I throw half of it away).  So I limit the number of times I stop.  Fortunately for me I stopped at the Subway at 37th and Hwy 52.  I had the great guy that takes orders and says 'yes and no ma'am' and actually listens!!!  So my food was fresh, hot and exactly as ordered. 

If you want to visit a Subway I HIGHLY recommend this location - especially in the a.m. hours.  Why not stop for breakfast and get a lunch sandwich to go as well?

data.title: Last Time Buyer
data.text: Had a breakfast wrap made midmorning. It tasted a lot like something I ate in the military. Made and packaged in 1950 and opened up in 1968 to eat. No taste with a rubbery feel. Now I know why I am not a Subway  aficianado.
